# MAME
#
# MAME stands for Multiple Arcade Machine Emulator. When used in conjunction
# with images of the original arcade game's ROM and disk data, MAME attempts
# to reproduce that game as faithfully as possible on a more modern
# general-purpose computer. MAME can currently emulate several thousand
# different classic arcade video games from the late 1970s through the modern
# era.
#
# http://mamedev.org/
# https://github.com/mamedev/mame
# http://mameosx.sourceforge.net/
brew cask install mame

